<br>
1. /disc XXXXX . useful ? some are, some are not. duration vs. recast way out of sync. (/disc mighty strike your crit for XX you crit for XX you are stunned [for 8 seconds ] you can no longer blah blah). wait 60 min rinse, repeat. <br>
<br>
2. Taunt. (don't make me laugh) just doesn't work in high end game. i figure by the time i am 200 at taunt i should be able to say something about the mobs mother that will keep it focused one me for a good long time. sadly this is not true. <br>
<br>
3. AA. (hmmm where to start) <br>
<br>
bind wound - who actually used bind wound at lvl 59-60 ? you should have a BP with invig by then. <br>
<br>
Warcry - so warriors can raise resistance fear for the entire group for a short time (shouldn't the berserker be immune to fear all together ?) <br>
<br>
A quote from the eqlive website lets take a look :<br>
<br>
&quot;Warriors are the masters of armed combat in all its many forms ( unless you count Piercing, kick, hand to hand and such ). They are right at home on the battlefield and are trained to take as much punishment as they dole out( i could only wish i could dole out as much punishment as i get from a luclin mob), because of their innately strong constitutions. &quot;A warrior is not made,&quot; they say, &quot;a warrior is born,&quot; and so it is. Those who prove themselves to be hardier than others are perfectly suited for the rigors of this class ( well lets list who can be a hardy [aka dmg and HP equivalant]to warriors: shadow knights, Paladins, rangers, monks). Though slow to regain their considerable health ( lol too easy ) when injured, warriors are excellent companions for healer types (yep right after every class that can heal themselves ). Only the Erudite and high elf races do not produce warriors.&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't mean to be bitter so lets end this with some possible solutions that would put warriors back on track:<br>
<br>
1. Taunt that lasts. lets provide warriors of all levels the ability to maintain aggro. <br>
<br>
2. kick damage upgrade. how about different dmg for boots you wear? or procs on boots or something. i do about the same damage with kick at 54 as i did at 20. <br>
<br>
3. lets reduce the reuse/duration of /disc. i understand it takes a little time to restock the fires but this is silly. <br>
<br>
4. stuns fear - how about a AA that will prevent warriors from being stunned or feared. call it berserker. picture a dwarf foaming at the mouth attacking everything in sight, no matter how many time you hit him he doesn't run or get knocked down.<br>
<br>
Warriors are a class for those of us who like to be in the thick of it. VI seems determined to pull us out and have us sit at home while the new and improved melees go play. I want to be the hero pulling the beastie off my friends with my bare hands. <br>
<br>
thanks for taking the time to read my post. i admit i am not the expert in being a warrior but it is a start feel free to make other suggestions. <br>
<br>
thanks <br>
